Explore our stunning exhibitions, create art, and enjoy interactive performances. Free Admission | Entrada gratuita Open to the Public | Abierto al público Thank you to our campus and community partners in presenting this event! ¡Les damos las gracias a nuestros socios del campus y a la comunidad por presentar este evento! description: Kick off the spring semester with a warm cup of hot chocolate and explore exciting study abroad opportunities! Stop by the Study Abroad Office at 102 College Avenue to: - Learn about the 130+ programs we offer around the world - Chat with study abroad advisors and study abroad alumni - Be entered into a study abroad application fee waiver raffle We'll see you there!
name: Welcome Week: Study Abroad Hot Chocolate Open House

description: AUG is holding its annual Genetics Faculty Meet and Greet on Friday, January 24th, 2025 at 4:00 PM(exact time is subject to change) in the Life Sciences Building Atrium on Busch!  Students will rotate through tables of faculty grouped by research topic. Many of the faculty may be looking for undergrads to join their labs in the fall semester, so this is a good chance to learn about labs in the Genetics Department and meet professors and other students!    This event is open to all majors, so even if you aren't planning to major in Genetics, you can still attend! We will also provide refreshments.    Please fill out this form using your netID email to RSVP: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdtxLP-Zv709PmZuUetu2h_e233feq2OgUzkt558K3yTjCmjA/viewform
name: Genetics Meet and Greet

Join YEC as we discuss the upcoming semester over pizza! Help us give back to the New Brunswick community and continue to create volunteer opportunities for Rutgers students. All are welcome - we hope to see you there!
location: Cap & Skull Room 413 - College Avenue Student Center

description: The Office of Student Involvement & Leadership week is doing an open mic night, as part of our Student Involvement & Leadership week! During this event students will be able to perform, whether it is spoken word, dancing, singing, sharing art or any other forms of expression! This will be a great way to showcase your talent, support your peers, meet new people, enjoy food, and have fun!
name: Student Involvement & Leadership Week: Open Mic Night

description: This design lab will bring together students, faculty and staff together with food waste recycling and reutilization experts. Participants will hear the food waste related views, technology options and current practices and will be guided on creating ideas to bring sustainable solutions to food waste matters at Robert Wood Johnson Hospital
name: Design Lab: Exploring Sustainable Food Waste Recycling & Reutilization at RWJ Hospital

description: SparkNight is the free art party at the Zimmerli, inviting everyone to explore art, engage their creativity, and have fun!   Celebrate Black History Month with performances, music, artmaking, and pop-up tours that highlight contributions of African American and African Diasporic Artists. Free and open to the public. Complimentary light refreshments. Food available for purchase from food truck outside the Zimmerli.   Specials thanks to our campus and community partners for their support: Crossroads Theatre | Paul Robeson Cultural Center | Rutgers SJE
name: SparkNight: Celebrating Black History Month
organizationNames: Center for Social Justice Education and LGBT Communities (Rutgers University)

description: Every year, the BOLD Center hosts a career conference to empower students through career planning, discuss topics related to Women in Work, and meet other women professionals in a variety of industries to share their wealth of knowledge. Learn tips and tools for starting off your career, how to navigate difficult situations, and the best ways to make your mark in the workplace. There will be food, giveaways, prizes and networking opportunities.
name: Christiana Foglio DC'84 Douglass Career Conference
organizationName: The BOLD Center at Douglass for Leadership, Career and Personal Development

description: Join us for a vibrant and immersive Carnival-themed celebration honoring Latine culture! This lively event will feature colorful costumes, traditional music, dance performances, and delicious Latinx cuisine. Experience the rich diversity of Latine traditions through art, storytelling, and community engagement, as we come together to celebrate the beauty, history, and creativity of Latine communities. Don't miss out on this exciting cultural extravaganza—bring your family, friends, and festive spirit!
name: Último Domingo: Carnaval (Last Sunday: Carnival)
organizationNames: Center for Latino Arts and Culture
